🧠 UI / CONTROLLER ENGINE
Governance System for Record View Engine (Authoritative)
🔷 0. PURPOSE

The UI / Controller Engine is the governing layer of the entire system.

It is responsible for:

controlling all user interactions
governing all execution entry points
enforcing system patterns
maintaining UI ↔ server consistency
orchestrating workflows and reconciliation
🔑 Core Definition

🔥 The UI renders the system — the Controller governs it

🔷 1. WHAT THE ENGINE CONTROLS

The UI / Controller Engine governs:

Record View lifecycle
Section lifecycle
Section Item lifecycle
Allocation lifecycle
Saving system
Reconciliation system
Workflow execution (workers)

👉 It is the runtime brain of the Record View Engine

🔷 2. ENGINE POSITION IN SYSTEM
UI (render surface)
    ↓
CONTROLLER ENGINE (governor)
    ↓
Transport → Application → Domain → Data → Infra
UI = display + input
Controller = decision + orchestration
Backend layers = execution
🔷 3. UI LAYER — ENGINE SURFACE
Responsibilities
Render:
Record shell
Sections
